{{fr-interjection}}

# {{lb|fr|idiomatic|informal|childish or old}} {{l|en|really}} ''(used when you want to emphasize that something is true)''
#* {{quote|fr|Moi je sais jouer au foot, '''vrai de vrai''' ! Pas vrai Alceste ?|I know how to play football! Isn't it true Alceste?}}

{{fr-noun|m|f=une vraie de vraie|des vrais de vrais}}

# {{lb|fr|rare|old}} {{l|en|lout}}, {{l|en|bandit}}, {{l|en|thug}}
#* {{quote|fr|Ce mec c'est un '''vrai de vrai''' : il se prend une baffe, deux, trois, et il bronche même pas !|That fella is a real thug: he gets smacked once, a second time, a third, and he doesn't even react!}}
# {{l|en|real}} ''(used to insist on the fact that something or someone has all the characteristics to be called in some way)''
#* {{quote|fr|Je veux un homme, '''un vrai de vrai''', qui peut transporter n'importe quoi sans jamais sourciller.|I want a real man, who can carries anything without ever batting an eye.}}
